<p>
Layers can be merged using other methods than their Alpha.
These are available in the "Mode" combo-box of the layers dialog.
</p>

<table class="mydemo">
<tr class="mydemo">
<td class="mydemo">

<h3>Demo</h3>

<ol>

<li>
Generate an image with <menupath>&lt;Toolbox&gt; -&gt; Xtns -&gt; Script-Fu -&gt; Patterns -&gt; "3D Truchet"</menupath>.
</li>
<li>
Duplicate the layer using <menupath>&lt;Layers&gt; -&gt; Duplicate Layer</menupath>.
</li>
<li>
Render a nice gradient on the lower layer.
</li>
<li>
Change the mode of the upper layer to Screen.
</li>
<li>
Switch the mode to Addition and then to Subtract and to to other
modes.
</li>

</ol>

